V{{Infobox philosopher\u000a| region           = Western Philosophy\u000a| era              = [[21st-century philosophy]]\u000a| image            = Mario Kopic 2007.jpg\u000a| name             = Mario Kopi\u0107\u000a| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1965|03|13}}\u000a| birth_place      = [[Dubrovnik]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavia]]\u000a| school_tradition = [[continental philosophy]], [[existentialism]], [[Phenomenology (philosophy)|phenomenology]]\u000a| main_interests   = [[Ethics]], [[Religion]], [[Culture]]\u000a| influences       = [[Friedrich Nietzsche]], [[Martin Heidegger]], [[Hannah Arendt]], [[Jacques Derrida]],  [[Gianni Vattimo]], [[Reiner Schürmann]]\u000a| notable_ideas    =\u000a}}\u000a\u000a'''Mario Kopi\u0107''' (born 13 March 1965) is a [[philosopher]], [[author]] and [[translator]]. His main areas of interest include: [[History of Ideas]], [[Philosophy of Art]], [[Philosophy of Culture]], [[Phenomenology (philosophy)|Phenomenology]] and [[Philosophy of Religion]].<ref>http://www.zarez.hr/clanci/razgovor-s-mariom-kopicem</ref><ref>http://www.danas.rs/dodaci/vikend/knjiga_danas/ili_cemo_naci_smisao_ili_cemo_se_izgubiti</ref>\u000a\u000aKopi\u0107 is influenced by and writes extensively on [[Friedrich Nietzsche]], [[Martin Heidegger]], [[Hannah Arendt]], [[Jacques Derrida]], [[Gianni Vattimo]], [[Reiner Schürmann]] and [[Du\u0161an Pirjevec]]. He also translated works by Nietzsche (''[[Thus Spoke Zarathustra]]'', ''[[On the Genealogy of Morality]]''), [[Giorgio Agamben]], Gianni Vattimo, Jacques Derrida and Du\u0161an Pirjevec into [[Croatian language|Croatian]].\u000a\u000a==Life and work==\u000aMario Kopi\u0107 was born in [[Dubrovnik]], [[Croatia]]. He studied [[Philosophy]] and [[Comparative Literature]] at the [[University of Zagreb]]; [[Phenomenology (philosophy)|Phenomenology]] and [[Anthropology]] at the [[University of Ljubljana]]; [[History of Ideas]] at the ''Institute Friedrich Meinecke'' at the [[Free University of Berlin]] (under the mentorship of [[Ernst Nolte]]); and [[Comparative Religion]] and [[Anthropology of religion]] at the [[Sapienza University of Rome]] (under the mentorship of Ida Magli).<ref>http://www.hrvatskodrustvopisaca.hr/hr/dogadanje/biblioteka-tvrda-nova-knjiga-marija-kopica-117</ref>\u000a\u000aMario Kopi\u0107's philosophical work is under the influence of the [[Italy|Italian]] philosophical approach known as ''pensiero debole''<ref>http://www.odjek.ba/?broj=16&id=17</ref> or "weak thought", the [[political]] thought of [[Hannah Arendt|Arendt]],<ref>http://pescanik.net/2011/10/hannah-arendt-lijevo-ili-desno/</ref><ref>http://pescanik.net/2010/12/misljenje-bez-sjaja-slave/</ref> and the [[ethical]]-political thought of late [[Jacques Derrida|Derrida]].<ref>http://pescanik.net/2013/08/mislilac-nove-eticnosti/</ref>\u000a\u000aIn his latest works ''The Unhealable Wound of the World'', ''The Challenges of the Post-metaphysics'', ''Sextant'' and ''The Beats of the Other'' Kopi\u0107 developed a kind of onto-politics of liberal-conservative [[postmodernism]] and the post-anthropocentric [[humanism]].<ref>http://www.komunikacija.org.rs/komunikacija/casopisi/fid/XXI_2/15/download_ser_lat</ref> For him the world is the space of [[being]] as event, and only then the arena of national and social or political conflict.<ref>http://www.odjek.ba/eng/index.php?broj=02&id=06</ref> The world, or existence, is our ontological responsibility, which precedes political, judicial and moral responsibility.<ref>http://zlaticahoke.blogspot.hr/2016/01/internet-and-philosophy.html/</ref>\u000a\u000aKopi\u0107 appears in [[Igor Ivanov Izi]]'s 1995 film N.E.P.<ref name="N.E.P.-1995">http://m.imdb.com/name/nm0465784/</ref>\u000a\u000a==Published books==\u000a* Art and Philosophy: An Anthology (''Filozofija i umjetnost - Antologija''), Delo 11-12 /1990, [[Belgrade]] 1990.\u000a* Experiencing the Margins of the Sense (''Isku\u0161avanje rubova smisla: pabirci iz estetike''), Dubrovnik 1991. \u000a* With Nietzsche on Europe (''S Nietzscheom o Europi''), [[Zagreb]] 2001.\u000a* [[Nietzsche]] and [[Evola]]: The Thought as Destiny (''Nietzsche e Evola: il pensiero come destino''), [[Rome]] 2001.\u000a* A Trial to the West (''Proces Zapadu''), Dubrovnik 2003. ISBN 953-7089-02-9\u000a* The Challenges of the Post-Metaphysics (''Izazovi post-metafizike''), [[Sremski Karlovci]] - [[Novi Sad]] 2007. ISBN 978-86-7543-120-6\u000a* The Unhealable Wound of the World (''Nezacjeljiva rana svijeta''), Zagreb 2007. ISBN 978-953-249-035-0\u000a* [[Gianni Vattimo]] Reader (Ed.),(''Gianni Vattimo: \u010citanka (Ur.)''), Zagreb 2008. ISBN 978-953-249-061-9\u000a* [[Du\u0161an Pirjevec]], Death and Nothing (ed.), (''Smrt i ni\u0161tina, (Ur.)'') Zagreb 2009. ISBN 978-953-225-124-1\u000a* Sextant: The Outlines of the Spiritual Foundations of the World (''Sekstant: Skice o duhovnim temeljima svijeta''), Belgrade 2010. ISBN 978-86-519-0449-6\u000a* The Beats of the Other (''Otkucaji drugoga''), Belgrade 2013. ISBN 978-86-519-1721-2\u000a* The Windows: Essays on Art and Literature (''Prozori: Ogledi o umjetnosti''), Dubrovnik 2015. ISBN 978-953-7835-24-8\u000a\u000a==See also==\u000a*[[Continental philosophy]]\u000a*[[Deconstruction-and-religion]]\u000a*[[Postmodern Christianity]]\u000a*[[Ontotheology]]\u000a*[[Phenomenology (philosophy)]]\u000a*[[Phenomenology of religion]]\u000a\u000a==References==\u000a{{reflist}}\u000a\u000a==Sources==\u000a*[http://www.zarez.hr/clanci/razgovor-s-mariom-kopicem Interview with Mario Kopi\u0107, Zarez, 2008] {{hr icon}}\u000a*[http://www.danas.rs/dodaci/vikend/knjiga_danas/ili_cemo_naci_smisao_ili_cemo_se_izgubiti.54.html?news_id=188866 Interview with Mario Kopi\u0107, Danas, 2010] {{sr icon}}\u000a*[http://www.dulist.hr/clanak/15382/kulturni-turizam-je-pornografija/ Interview with Mario Kopi\u0107, Dubrova\u010dki list, 2011] {{hr icon}}\u000a*[http://www.dulist.hr/mario-kopic-nema-velike-umjetnosti-koju-nije-posvetio-zivot/259156/ Interview with Mario Kopi\u0107, Dubrova\u010dki list, 2015] {{hr icon}}\u000a*[http://www.net.hr/kultura/knjiga/page/2007/07/23/0109006.html Nezacjeljiva rana svijeta] {{hr icon}}\u000a*[http://pescanik.net/2011/05/hannah-arendt-i-nacionalizam/ 2011 article by Mario Kopi\u0107 about Hannah Arendt]  {{hr icon}}\u000a*[http://pescanik.net/2012/08/misao-treceg-milenijuma/ 2012 article by Mario Kopi\u0107 about Heidegger]  {{hr icon}}\u000a*[http://pescanik.net/2013/08/mislilac-nove-eticnosti/ 2013 article by Mario Kopi\u0107 about Derrida]  {{hr icon}}\u000a*[http://filozofskimagazin.net/mario-kopic-schurmannova-misao-podrijetla/ 2015 article by Mario Kopi\u0107 about Reiner Schürmann] {{hr icon}}\u000a\u000a==External links==\u000a*[http://www.usm.maine.edu/bcj/issues/one/kopic.html Comments on Jacques Derrida's Les Spectres de Marx  by Mario Kopi\u0107]\u000a*[http://www.odjek.ba/eng/index.php?broj=02&id=06 Kafka and Nationalism by Mario Kopi\u0107]\u000a*[http://www.new-antaios.net/2013/02/heideggers-wiederholungsverstandnis-mario-kopic M. Kopi\u0107 Heideggers Wiederholungsverständnis 2013.] {{de icon}}\u000a*[http://www.new-antaios.net/2012/03/le-peuple-la-nation-et-limpouvoir-mario-kopic/ M. Kopi\u0107 Le peuple, la nation et l'(im)pouvoir 2012.] {{fr icon}}\u000a*[http://www.odjek.ba/index.php?broj=06&id=15 M. Kopi\u0107 Paul Ricoeur \u2013 filozof \u010ditanja 2005.] {{hr icon}}\u000a\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Kopic, Mario}}\u000a[[Category:1965 births]]\u000a[[Category:Living people]]\u000a[[Category:People from Dubrovnik]]\u000a[[Category:20th-century philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:21st-century philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Continental philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Phenomenologists]]\u000a[[Category:Heidegger scholars]]\u000a[[Category:Croatian philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:University of Ljubljana alumni]]\u000a[[Category:University of Zagreb alumni]]\u000a[[Category:Free University of Berlin alumni]]\u000a[[Category:Sap